<p><img border="0" height="19" src="http://www.byui.edu/comm/images/mission%20text.gif" width="139" /><br /> Graduates will show passion and respect for the power of communication and will apply principles and skills of successful, ethical communication in all areas of their lives. They will be well qualified to enter the professional workplace and obtain gainful and productive employment.</p>
<p>Graduates will understand and<em> </em>demonstrate these principles and skills through effectively:</p>
<ul>
<li>Interacting in one-on-one and group settings</li>
<li>Speaking and presenting to diverse audiences</li>
<li>Writing accurately, clearly, concisely and creatively across media-related styles and platforms</li>
<li>Implementing persuasive principles and tools of strategic planning to influence targeted audiences</li>
<li>Researching, analyzing and presenting data with clear and ethical interpretation and relevance</li>
<li>Communicating visually through proficiency with the latest tools of print, video and Web design and production</li>
<li>Understanding the history, roles and usage of traditional, online, mobile and social media</li>
<li>Communicating ethically and legally in all personal and professional settings while living and advocating the values and standards of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</li>
</ul>
